      "highlights" : "Wet snow requires caution.",
      "comment" : "As a consequence of new snow and wind, wind slabs formed in the last few days at high altitudes and in high Alpine regions. <br/> As a consequence of warming there will be a gradual increase in the avalanche danger. On very steep slopes the moist avalanches can be released naturally and reach medium size in isolated cases. <br/> Individual avalanche prone locations are to be found on very steep shady slopes above approximately 2600 m. Avalanches can be released, mostly by large loads and reach medium size."
